<br>
There is no way to fix the problem that macro farmers have created other than destroying the surplus that was created.  SOE isn't going to do that.<br>
<br>
If the bulk of excessive plat farms are corrected, the economy will eventually stabilize as all the excess plat gets redistributed.  But, that's going to require several iterations of people buying plat for $$ and spreading it among multiple vendors in the bazaar. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub147.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=oosoulwhisperoo>oo Soulwhisper oo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#330000>(3/24/04 1:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19198.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tax the bazaar!</span><hr size=1> this would create a black market...perhaps something in the Tunnels of EC where people would shout about the items they had for sale.  Can you imagine such a thing? <p>Bard<br>
