what problem are you trying to fix by taxing the bazaar?<br>
<br>
Pick any of your own, or the ones listed by Gneiss. Or this one: Brokers are keeping prices high?<br>
<br>
The brokers are a big problem, since the market is small and it is relatively easy to monopolize a certain item. The brokers are taking a risk by buying low and trying to sell high. Increase the brokers risk and this might fix itself. <br>
One way I could see is to keep them from reselling an item within a certain period of time (1 week?). That would force them to keep a much higher inventory, which costs them a lot to keep. <br>
Having them pay a tax would be corrected by the market most likely. One time fees or renting bazaar space would probably hurt the regular adventurer, who has 7 items for sale more. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=179894"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.comcast.net/~edmt/sig.JPG"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
