<br>
When you put an item in teh bazarre, you pay 10% of the price at that time. Then, the item stayed in the bazarre, at that price for 1 week, with or without your intervention. <br>
<br>
At the end of 1 week, the item auto returned to your inventory/bank if it hadn't sold. <br>
<br>
The big benefit, is that players wouldn't spam the market with tons of items that they really didn't think would sell.  And, they wouldn't put a loaf of bread for sale for 10,000 pp because it would cost them 1000 pp to do so.  <br>
<br>
However, for anyone that was selling the item and actually expected it to sell, it seemed to work well enough.  <br>
<br>
Although, now that I think about it, if I try to sell my fungi tunic for 50k or whatever the going rate is, ... I'm not sure I want to front the 5k for it. <br>
<br>
Hmmm.... Never mind, I take it back.  Do nothing, leave it alone.<br>
<br>
Wyndaria.  <p>Wyndaria, <br>
Maestro, The Nameless.<br>
